post_text: We are likely to have enrollment opportunities for this fall in our 10th grade class. While we still have a wait list, we also have several openings to fill and will be making offers in the next few weeks to complete our 10th grade roster. Please encourage interested families to submit an enrollment application as soon as possible to take advantage of this opportunity to get into our highly regarded adolescent program. Visit www.greatriverschool.org/enroll for more information on the application process! We are a tuition free public charter school, open to all students in Minnesota.

post_text:
For the Coffee House on 5/15, we're looking for video submissions from students and families at all levels. All performances will be pre-recorded and edited into a single video that will be streamed on the Blue Heron Bash event page Friday night. All submissions must be in by Wed May 13th!

If you are interested, here is the process:
-Record yourself performing.
-Please keep it in the three-minute range.
-Introduce yourself and let us know what you'll be performing.
-Make sure you are in good lighting so we can see you.
-Upload the video to Google Drive and share it with czieke@greatriverschool.org
-Any questions? Email Zack Scott: zscott@greatriverschool.org

post_text:
NoMythic competed this weekend at the Northern Lights regional in Duluth, where we rocked! The team ended qualification matches undefeated and ranked #1, and then went on to win finals and take FIRST PLACE, earning a spot at both the Minnesota State competition and World Championships.

Want to support the team's upcoming trip? Come out for our first fundraiser at the Naughty Greek this Wednesday evening from 6-8:30 pm. Come on down and celebrate with us! Check out our 2020 robot! Eat some amazing food. And help send this amazing team to the FIRST Championships!
text:
NoMythic competed this weekend at the Northern Lights regional in Duluth, where we rocked! The team ended qualification matches undefeated and ranked #1, and then went on to win finals and take FIRST PLACE, earning a spot at both the Minnesota State competition and World Championships.

Want to support the team's upcoming trip? Come out for our first fundraiser at the Naughty Greek this Wednesday evening from 6-8:30 pm. Come on down and celebrate with us! Check out our 2020 robot! Eat some amazing food. And help send this amazing team to the FIRST Championships!
